<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">//driving multipliers
    public static final double kLowSpeedMultiplier = 0.75;
    public static final double kMediumSpeedMultiplier = 0.9;
    public static final double kHighSpeedMultiplier = 1;

 private void configureDefaultDriveCommand() {
    m_drivetrain.setDefaultCommand(
      new RunCommand(() -&gt; {
          double speedMultiplier = speedChooser.getSelected();
           isFieldPositionEnabled = false;
              // Update the SmartDashboard with the current state after changing it
          SmartDashboard.putBoolean("Field Position Enabled", isFieldPositionEnabled);
          m_drivetrain.drive(
            -MathUtil.applyDeadband(m_driverController.getY(), OIConstants.kDriveDeadband) * speedMultiplier,
            -MathUtil.applyDeadband(m_driverController.getX(), OIConstants.kDriveDeadband) * speedMultiplier,
            -MathUtil.applyDeadband(m_driverController.getZ(), OIConstants.kDriveDeadband) * speedMultiplier,
            false, true);
        }, 
        m_drivetrain) 
    );
  }
</code></pre>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-07-05T16:39:53.513Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":283,"readers_count":282,"score":71.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":468343,"topic_slug":"do-you-replace-youre-swerve-once-in-a-while","display_username":"Brandon McDonald","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":20632,"username":"kingc95","name":"Mr. Siefen | 453","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/kingc95/{size}/226662_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62443,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FAMNM President"},"post_url":"/t/do-you-replace-youre-swerve-once-in-a-while/468343/7","custom_user_title":"FAMNM President","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3405548,"name":"Chris Bale","username":"cbale2000","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cbale2000/{size}/2142_2.png","created_at":"2024-07-05T17:30:29.471Z","cooked":"<p>When we first switched to Swerve a few years back, we built an entire swerve test platform in the off season, both for the drivers and the programmers to practice with. We found the practice to be extremely valuable and would definitely recommend having a practice robot (even if it’s just an old swerve robot) available.</p>
<p>As a general rule, we also keep all of our old robots as together as possible and buy new modules each season. This is both so we have test/demo robots that we can use, but also because robot hardware gets a LOT of abuse during a season. For most components, we prefer to buy new each season whenever possible. There are exceptions of course, for instance we generally move our Limelights between robots since vision isn’t as necessary on a practice/demo bot, but almost anything mechanical we prefer to replace if at all possible.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-07-05T17:30:29.471Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":242,"readers_count":241,"score":68.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":468343,"topic_slug":"do-you-replace-youre-swerve-once-in-a-while","display_username":"Chris Bale","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":6560,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/do-you-replace-youre-swerve-once-in-a-while/468343/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3405577,"name":"Roman A.","username":"RomanTechPlus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/romantechplus/{size}/214929_2.png","created_at":"2024-07-05T19:59:34.879Z","cooked":"